p-value and adjusted p-value analysis

One important note on false discovery rate (FDR):

  1. assume for now that we choose \(\alpha = 0.05\). Because we have total 26390 valid gene results, we would get theoretically \(26390\times 0.05\approx 1320\) false positives. As shown below we detected total of \(2998+2909=5907\) positives. Hence, our FDR could be \(\frac{1320}{5907}\approx 22\%\).

  2. This FDR of \(22\%\) seems too high to believe the gene list. We need to use to account for this. BH adjusted p-value means the FDR if we call significant all genes with smaller than/equal to p-adj as a given gene.

  3. It would be perhaps acceptable to set p-adj as 0.1, giving \(10\%\) false positives.

Also, note that DESeq automatically applies independent filtering based on baseMean column. Another way to do filtering is by independent hypothesis weighting.

First, p-value analysis:

# a quick function for pretty output of p-value dataframe results
df_pretty <- function(df,order_column, decre = FALSE, head_count=5,fmt="e",dig=2){
        df_temp <- df
        df_temp$row_name <- row.names(df_temp)
        as.data.frame(lapply(head(df_temp[order(df_temp[[order_column]], decreasing=decre),],head_count),formatC, format=fmt, digits=dig))
}
pvalue_threshold <- 0.05
res <- results(dds, contrast=c("zt","ZT22","ZT10"), alpha = pvalue_threshold) #Specify the contrast here
paste("genes with non-NA p-value result = ", as.character(sum(!is.na(res$pvalue))))
## [1] "genes with non-NA p-value result =  26395"
#mcols(res, use.names = TRUE) #shows structure of the dataframe.
#summary(res)
resSig.pvalue <- subset(res, pvalue < pvalue_threshold)
paste("genes with p-value below threshold", as.character(length(resSig.pvalue$pvalue)))
## [1] "genes with p-value below threshold 7353"
df_pretty(resSig.pvalue,"log2FoldChange")
df_pretty(resSig.pvalue,"log2FoldChange",decre=TRUE)

Second, adjusted p-value analysis:

padj_threshold <- 0.05
paste("genes with non-NA p-value result = ", as.character(sum(res$padj < padj_threshold, na.rm=TRUE)))
## [1] "genes with non-NA p-value result =  5907"
resSig.padj <- subset(res, padj < padj_threshold)
paste("genes with p-value below threshold", as.character(length(resSig.padj$pvalue)))
## [1] "genes with p-value below threshold 5907"
df_pretty(resSig.padj,"log2FoldChange")
df_pretty(resSig.padj,"log2FoldChange",decre=TRUE)
